{"title_page": "Bananarama discography", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2017}}\n{{Infobox artist discography\n|Artist      = [[Bananarama]]\n|Image       = Bananarama crop.jpg\n|Caption     = Bananarama live in Audley End in 2007.\n|Studio      = 11\n|Singles     = 45\n|EP          =\n|Compilation = 13\n|Live        =\n|Video       = 4\n}}\nThis article lists the [[discography]] of the British [[girl group]] [[Bananarama]].\n\n==Albums==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of albums, with selected chart positions, sales figures and certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"8\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\" | [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[UK Albums Chart|UK]]<br /><ref name=uk>UK chart peaks:\n*Top 100 peaks other than where specified below: {{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/30294/bananarama/|title=Official Charts > Bananarama|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=2016-04-25}} N.B. The Official Charts site erroneously duplicates the 3 April 1983 albums chart for the week 27 March 1983; hence \"Deep Sea Skiving\" is listed as peaking at #8 instead of #7.\n*''Deep Sea Skiving'' UK albums chart peak: {{cite web|url=http://scans.chartarchive.org/UK/1983/14%20-%2002%20Apr%20Record%20Mirror%20Albums.jpg|title=Top Albums & Tapes \u2013 Week Ending April 2, 1983|publisher=chartarchive.org|accessdate=2016-04-25}}\n*Top 200 peaks from November 1994 to December 2010: {{cite web|url=https://www.zobbel.de/cluk/CLUK_B.HTM|title=Chart Log UK 1994\u20132010 > Darren B \u2013 David Byrne|publisher=Dipl.-Bibl.(FH) Tobias Zywietz|accessdate=2015-08-13}}\n*UK peaks for \"Aie a Mwana\" and \"Tripping on Your Love\" taken from the liner notes of the ''In a Bunch: The Singles 1981\u20131993'' box set, released through Edsel Records, 2015.</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br /><ref name=aus>Australian peak chart positions:\n*[[Kent Music Report]] peaks:\n**Top 100 peaks to 12 June 1988: {{cite book|last=Kent |first=David |authorlink=David Kent (historian)|title=Australian Chart Book 1970\u20131992|publisher=Australian Chart Book|location = Sydney|year=1993|edition=Illustrated|pages=25\u201326|isbn=0-646-11917-6}} N.B. The Kent Report chart was licensed by [[Australian Recording Industry Association|ARIA]] between mid-1983 and 12 June 1988.\n*[[ARIA Charts|ARIA Chart]] peaks:\n**Top 50 peaks from 13 June 1988: {{cite web|url=https://australian-charts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Bananarama|title=australian-charts.com > Bananarama in Australian Charts|publisher=Hung Medien |accessdate=2015-10-02}}\n**Top 100 peaks from January 1990 to December 2010: {{cite book|last=Ryan|first=Gavin|title=Australia's Music Charts 1988\u20132010|year=2011|publisher=Moonlight Publishing|location=Mt. Martha, VIC, Australia|edition=PDF|page=23}}\n**\"Nathan Jones\": {{cite web|url=https://i.imgur.com/j7baC6b.png|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129020822/http://i.imgur.com/j7baC6b.png|archivedate=29 November 2014|url-status=live|title=Response from ARIA re: chart inquiry, received 17 January 2014|accessdate=2015-10-02|publisher=Imgur.com }}\n**\"Only Your Love\": {{cite web|url=https://i.imgur.com/AXKd0SE.png|title=The ARIA Australian Top 100 Singles Chart \u2013 Week Ending 28 Oct 1990 (1\u201360)|accessdate=2016-04-19 |publisher=Imgur.com }}\n**\"Preacher Man\", \"Long Train Running\" and \"Movin' On\": {{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129020821/http://i.imgur.com/9AQCjII.jpg|url=https://i.imgur.com/9AQCjII.jpg|archivedate=29 November 2014|title=Response from ARIA re: chart inquiry, received 17 June 2014|accessdate=2015-10-02|publisher=Imgur.com|url-status=live}}\n**\"Cruel Summer '89\", \"Every Shade of Blue\" and \"Take Me to Your Heart\": {{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150605213523/http://i.imgur.com/DkGCr8v.jpg|url=https://i.imgur.com/DkGCr8v.jpg |archivedate=5 June 2015|title=Response from ARIA re: chart inquiry, received 5 June 2015|accessdate=2015-10-02|publisher=Imgur.com|url-status=live}}\n**''Pop Life'': {{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150716153430/http://i.imgur.com/oyPN1pW.jpg|url=https://i.imgur.com/oyPN1pW.jpg|archivedate=16 July 2015|title=Response from ARIA re: chart inquiry, received 15 July 2015|accessdate=2015-10-02|publisher=Imgur.com|url-status=live}}\n**''Please Yourself'': {{cite web|url=https://i.imgur.com/9ehjEFX.gif|title=Response from ARIA re: chart inquiry, received 13 September 2016|publisher=Imgur.com|accessdate=2016-09-13}}\n**''Ultra Violet'' and ''Drama'': {{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151109062955/http://i.imgur.com/KqVcpbl.jpg|title=Response from ARIA re: chart inquiry, received 9 November 2015 |url=https://i.imgur.com/KqVcpbl.jpg|archivedate=9 November 2015|accessdate=2015-11-09|publisher=Imgur.com|url-status=live}}\n**\"Look on the Floor (Hypnotic Tango)\": {{cite web|url=https://pandora.nla.gov.au/pan/23790/20060920-0000/issue865.pdf|title=The ARIA Report \u2013 Issue #865 > Week Commencing 2nd October 2006 |publisher=[[Pandora Archive]]|accessdate=2016-04-19}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Canadian Albums Chart|CAN]]<br/><ref name=\"can\">{{cite web|url=http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-110.01-e.php?PHPSESSID=v2a76h62to0aart05gg0u3agj2&q1=Bananarama&q2=Top+Albums%2FCDs&interval=20|title=RPM Top Albums/CDs \u2013 Bananarama|work=[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]|publisher=[[Library and Archives Canada]]|accessdate=2010-10-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220064325/http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-110.01-e.php?PHPSESSID=v2a76h62to0aart05gg0u3agj2&q1=Bananarama&q2=Top+Albums%2FCDs&interval=20|archive-date=20 December 2016|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[GfK Entertainment Charts|GER]]<br/><ref name=ger>{{cite web|url=https://www.offiziellecharts.de/suche?artist_search=Bananarama&do_search=do|title=Offizielle Deutsche Charts > Suchen nach \"Bananarama\"|language=German|publisher=GfK Entertainment|accessdate=2020-02-22}} N.B. Select the 'Album' tab to display albums chart peaks.</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Recording Industry Association of New Zealand|NZ]]<br/><ref name=nz>{{cite web|url=https://charts.nz/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Bananarama|title=charts.org.nz > Bananarama in New Zealand Charts|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=2019-03-14}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Sverigetopplistan|SWE]]<br/><ref name=swedish>{{cite web|url=https://swedishcharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Bananarama|title=swedischarts.com > Bananarama in Swedish Charts|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=2011-10-30}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Swiss Hitparade|SWI]]<br/><ref name=swi>Swiss chart peaks:\n*Albums: {{cite web|url=https://hitparade.ch/search.asp?search=bananarama&cat=a|title=hitparade.ch > Suchen nach: Bananarama (Alben)|language=German|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=2020-02-22}}\n*Singles: {{cite web|url=https://hitparade.ch/search.asp?search=bananarama&cat=s|title=hitparade.ch > Suchen nach: Bananarama (Songs)|language=German|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=2020-02-22}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Billboard 200|US]]<br/><ref name=billboard>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/bananarama/chart-history/TLP|title=Billboard > Bananarama Chart History > Billboard 200|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=2020-02-22}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| '''''[[Deep Sea Skiving]]'''''\n|\n*Released: 7 March 1983\n*Label: [[London Records|London]]\n*Formats: [[LP record|LP]], [[Compact Cassette|cassette]], CD\n| 7 || 85 || 48 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || 63 \n|\n* [[British Phonographic Industry|UK]]: Silver<ref name=\"bpi certs\">{{cite web|url=https://i.imgur.com/Nimmeib.jpg|title=BPI > Certified Awards > Search results for 'Bananarama' (from bpi.co.uk)|publisher=[[British Phonographic Industry]]|via=Imgur.com|accessdate=2016-07-23}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| '''''[[Bananarama (album)|Bananarama]]'''''\n|\n*Released: 16 April 1984\n*Label: London\n*Formats: LP, cassette, CD\n| 16 || 99 || \u2014 || 45 || \u2014 || \u2014 || 9 || 30\n|\n* UK: Silver<ref name=\"bpi certs\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| '''''[[True Confessions (album)|True Confessions]]'''''\n|\n*Released: 7 July 1986\n*Label: London\n*Formats: LP, cassette, CD\n| 46 || 19 || 10 || 25 || 33 || \u2014 || 6 || 15\n|\n* [[Music Canada|CAN]]: Platinum<ref name=\"Music Canada\">\"[http://www.musiccanada.com/gpSearchResult.aspx Certified Awards Search] {{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/6B59B5BCL?url=http://www.musiccanada.com/gpSearchResult.aspx |date=2012-10-01 }}\". [[Music Canada]]. Retrieved on 2011-10-30. Note: User needs to enter \"Bananarama\" in the \"Search\" field, \"Artist\" in the \"Search by\" field and click the \"Go\" button. Select \"More info\" next to the relevant entry to see full certification history.</ref>\n* [[Recording Industry Association of America|US]]: Gold<ref name=\"riaa\">{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH |title=Searchable Database |publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America]] |accessdate=2011-10-30 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070626050454/http://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH |archivedate=26 June 2007}} Note: User must define 'Artist' search parameter as \"Bananarama\".</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| '''''[[Wow! (Bananarama al