{"title_page": "2020 Artsakhian general election", "text_new": "{{current election}}\n{{Infobox election\n| election_name = 2020 Artsakhian general election\n| country = Artsakh\n| type = presidential\n| previous_election = 2017 Artsakhian presidential election\n| previous_year = 2017\n| election_date = 31 March 2020\n| next_election = [[Artsakh general election, 2025]]\n| next_year = 2025\n| title = [[President of Artsakh|President]]\n| before_election = [[Bako Sahakyan]]\n| before_party = Independent (politician)\n| posttitle = \n| after_election = \n| after_party = \n| ongoing = No\n}}\n\n'''General elections''' where held in the unrecognised [[Republic of Artsakh]] on 31 March 2020. Voters will elect the [[President of Artsakh|President]] and 33 members of the [[National Assembly (Artsakh)|National Assembly]]. It will be the first time the President and National Assembly are elected at the same time.\n\n== Background ==\nPresidential elections were initially scheduled to be held by popular vote in 2017, five years after the [[Nagorno-Karabakh presidential election, 2012|2012 elections]]. However, after a [[Nagorno-Karabakh constitutional referendum, 2017|constitutional referendum]] in 2017, the country switched from a [[semi-presidential system]] to a [[presidential system]]. As a result, in the [[2017 Artsakhian presidential election|2017 presidential elections]] the [[National Assembly (Artsakh)|National Assembly]] [[Artsakhian presidential election, 2017|re-elected]] [[Bako Sahakyan]] as President for the next three years until the general election.<ref>[http://media-center.am/en/1487755829 The new constitution of Artsakh will lead to concentration of power and resources] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170820122417/http://media-center.am/en/1487755829 |date=20 August 2017}} Media Centre, 21 February 2017</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mediamax.am/en/news/karabakh/24374/|title=Bako Sahakyan re-elected President of Artsakh|work=mediamax.am|access-date=22 July 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe incumbent [[President of Artsakh|President]] [[Bako Sahakyan]] declared that he will not run in the elections.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.civilnet.am/news/2018/06/11/\u0532\u0561\u056f\u0578-\u054d\u0561\u0570\u0561\u056f\u0575\u0561\u0576\u0568-2020-\u056b\u0576-\u0579\u056b-\u0561\u057c\u0561\u057b\u0561\u0564\u0580\u057e\u056b-\u0576\u0561\u056d\u0561\u0563\u0561\u0570\u056b-\u057a\u0561\u0577\u057f\u0578\u0576\u0578\u0582\u0574/339136|title=\u0532\u0561\u056f\u0578 \u054d\u0561\u0570\u0561\u056f\u0575\u0561\u0576\u0568 2020-\u056b\u0576 \u0579\u056b \u0561\u057c\u0561\u057b\u0561\u0564\u0580\u057e\u056b \u0576\u0561\u056d\u0561\u0563\u0561\u0570\u056b \u057a\u0561\u0577\u057f\u0578\u0576\u0578\u0582\u0574|website=www.civilnet.am|language=hy|access-date=1 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.azatutyun.am/a/29284056.html|title=\u0532\u0561\u056f\u0578 \u054d\u0561\u0570\u0561\u056f\u0575\u0561\u0576\u0568 \u0570\u0561\u0575\u057f\u0561\u0580\u0561\u0580\u0565\u056c \u0567 2020-\u056b\u0576 \u0579\u0561\u057c\u0561\u057b\u0561\u0564\u0580\u057e\u0565\u056c\u0578\u0582 \u0578\u0580\u0578\u0577\u0574\u0561\u0576 \u0574\u0561\u057d\u056b\u0576|website=\u00ab\u0531\u0566\u0561\u057f \u0535\u057e\u0580\u0578\u057a\u0561/\u0531\u0566\u0561\u057f\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0578\u0582\u0576\u00bb \u057c\u0561\u0564\u056b\u0578\u056f\u0561\u0575\u0561\u0576|language=hy|access-date=1 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Electoral system ==\nThe [[President of Artsakh]] is elected using the [[two-round system]]. If a candidate takes more than 50% of the overall vote, he or she is declared elected. If the 50% threshold is not met by any candidate, a second round of voting is held. In the second round, only the two most popular candidates from the first round may participate. The winner of the second round is elected President of Artsakh.\n\nMembers of the [[National Assembly (Artsakh)|National Assembly]] will be elected by [[proportional representation]], with between 27 and 33 MPs; the number will be defined by the Electoral Code.<ref>[http://www.nankr.am/en/1838 Article 107] Constitution of the Republic of Artsakh</ref>\n\n== Potential presidential candidates ==\n<!--DO NOT ADD CANDIDATES WITHOUT A SOURCE-->\n* [[Arayik Harutyunyan]], President's advisor, former [[Prime Minister of Artsakh|Prime Minister]] and [[State Minister of Artsakh|State Minister]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://armtimes.com/hy/article/143432|title=\u0548\u055e\u057e \u0567 \u0570\u0561\u057e\u0561\u056f\u0576\u0578\u0582\u0574 2020 \u0569\u057e\u0561\u056f\u0561\u0576\u056b\u0576 \u0564\u0561\u057c\u0576\u0561\u056c \u0531\u0580\u0581\u0561\u056d\u056b \u0576\u0561\u056d\u0561\u0563\u0561\u0570. \u0568\u0576\u0564\u0564\u056b\u0574\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0578\u0582\u0576\u0568 \u056c\u0578\u0582\u0580\u057b \u0567 \u057f\u0580\u0561\u0574\u0561\u0564\u0580\u057e\u0561\u056e|website=Armtimes.com|language=hy|access-date=1 February 2019}}</ref>\n* [[:hy:\u0544\u0561\u057d\u056b\u057d \u0544\u0561\u0575\u056b\u056c\u0575\u0561\u0576|Masis Mayilyan]], current Foreign Affairs Minister<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aysor.am/en/news/2020/02/12/mayilyan-babayan/1658791|title=Candidacies of Artsakh FM Masis Mayilyan, President spokesperson Davit Babayan nominated at upcoming presidential elections in Artsakh - aysor.am - Hot news from Armenia|first=Helix Consulting|last=LLC|website=www.aysor.am}}</ref>\n* [[Vitaly Balasanyan]], former Secretary of the National Security Council of Artsakh<ref>{{Citation|title=\u054e\u056b\u057f\u0561\u056c\u056b \u0532\u0561\u056c\u0561\u057d\u0561\u0576\u0575\u0561\u0576\u0568 \u0579\u056b \u0562\u0561\u0581\u0561\u057c\u0578\u0582\u0574\u055d 2020-\u056b\u0576 \u056f\u0561\u0580\u0578\u0572 \u0567 \u057a\u0561\u0575\u0584\u0561\u0580\u0565\u056c \u053c\u0542 \u0576\u0561\u056d\u0561\u0563\u0561\u0570\u056b \u057a\u0561\u0577\u057f\u0578\u0576\u056b \u0570\u0561\u0574\u0561\u0580|url=https://www.azatutyun.am/a/28630642.html|language=hy|access-date=1 February 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Ashot Ghoulyan]], current leader of the [[Democratic Party of Artsakh]]<ref>{{Citation|title=Democratic Congress 2020 Ashot Ghulyan has been nominated for the presidential election|url=http://www.dpa.am/wp/archives/3850?lang=hyl|language=hy|access-date=15 January 2020}}</ref>\n<!--DO NOT ADD CANDIDATES WITHOUT A SOURCE-->\n\n==Conduct==\nSeveral members of the [[United States Congress]] announced that their office employees and senior advisers would visit Artsakh to observe the elections. Congressman [[Frank Pallone]] stated that \"We want to highlight that democracy works in Artsakh and is in accordance with all the standards of free society.\"<ref>{{Citation|title=Several US Congressmen to send their office staffers to Artsakh to observe elections|url=https://armenpress.am/eng/news/1005462.html|access-date=19 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International reaction==\nThe [[European Union]],<ref>[https://mediamax.am/en/news/karabakh/37115/ EU doesn\u2019t recognize the \u201clegal framework\u201d of NK elections]. ''News.am''. 31 March 2020.</ref> the [[OSCE Minsk Group]],<ref>[https://www.osce.org/minsk-group/449410 Press Statement by the Co-Chairs of the OSCE Minsk Group]. OSCE. 31 March 2020.</ref> [[NATO]],<ref>[https://caucasuswatch.de/news/2561.html Nagorno-Karabakh: elections despite pandemic and international criticism]. Caucasus Watch. 31 March 2020.</ref> the [[Organisation of Islamic Cooperation]],<ref>[https://www.oic-oci.org/topic/?t_id=23305&t_ref=13971&lan=fr L'OCI rejette la tenue d'\u00e9lections dans le Nagorno-Karabakh occup\u00e9]. 31 March 2020</ref> the [[GUAM Organization for Democracy and Economic Development]],<ref>[https://en.trend.az/azerbaijan/karabakh/3215786.html GUAM condemns so-called \u201celections\u201d in Azerbaijan\u2019s occupied territories]. ''Trend''. 31 March 2020</ref> the [[Turkic Council|Cooperation Council of Turkic-Speaking States]]<ref>[https://www.turkkon.org/en/haberler/statement-by-the-cooperation-council-of-turkic-speaking-states_1986 STATEMENT BY THE COOPERATION COUNCIL OF TURKIC SPEAKING STATES]. 31 March 2020. </ref> and the governments and embassies of [[Azerbaijan]],<ref>[https://azertag.az/en/xeber/Illegal_elections_in_the_occupied_territories_of_the_Republic_of_Azerbaijan-1434601?__cf_chl_jschl_tk__=9bcaa707a104cb2b63975814e88fcfc320c1d715-1585691544-0-AQIfyO7FOldR6ofqPeoJ9MIxhzwc2UcKSPA7m2GYBfM-5caTAe4Sw06MiXX2p1NDMs5Pjnzw5d06DeMGiDXE5cVL2a7F2ROaF2ZF6Vprbj8p7DuzvhqFpJ-ZnIMM2TUvWEaQs3zyC9LJL-CTvRz6kGmib8z46YYM0HnrvFQpg9bjyFj_jrmgrytQqrBY58oFzB5FWyL2fv5JHYKjEYYBMwK0LjHMonnIvEZI3H0pJ0z-tuSvoEFMIzS_ya4QYgGGVjtcAZ4CW_tQ7CcZdzXiGvQILaNGf23PM9DwU9PkXv0VZbc6VCvBgI4XrohibdOQu-HVQz1iVjbJ8DSrOkE6mtJebMfFa14PbNMJ9BJZPDXtUBAjyU4gAlVrLt6fXdgB_JQcw74nvnxd0vjq235Iids Illegal \u201celections\u201d in the occupied territories of the Republic of Azerbaijan]. ''Azertag''. 6 March 2020.</ref> [[Canada]],<ref>[https://twitter.com/CanEmbTurkey/status/1245350594174488577 Canada supports the territorial integrity Azerbaijan and doesn\u2019t recognize the so-called \u201celections\u201d held in Nagorno-Karabakh on 31/3]. Embassy of Canada in Turkey (accredited in Azerbaijan). Twitter. 1 April 2020.</ref> [[Estonia]],<ref>[https://twitter.com/MFAestonia/status/1244942719522344960 Estonia MFA: Estonia does not consider the so-called elections in Nagorno Karabakh as legitimate. We continue to support the mediation efforts of the OSCE Minsk Group Co-Chairs.]. Twitter.</ref> [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]],<ref>Ana Dumbadze. [http://georgiatoday.ge/news/20339/Georgian-MFA-Doesn Georgian MFA: We Don't Recognize \"Elections\" in N. Kharabkh]. Georgia Today. 1 April 2020.</ref> [[Germany]],<ref>[https://twitter.com/GERonOstpolitik/status/1245225729534709761 We do not recognize the legal framework of the so called \u201epresidential and parliamentary elections\u201c that took place yesterday in #Nagorno-Karabakh. Both the elections and their results are considered illegal.] Michael Siebert. Twitter. 1 April 2020.</ref> [[Italy]],<ref>[https://twitter.com/ItalyMFA/status/1245036080094724097 No recogniton of the so-called presidential and parliamentary elections in #NagornoKarabakh by Italy.]. Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Italy. Twitter.</ref> [[Latvia]],<ref>[https://twitter.com/Latvian_MFA/status/1244981945798479875 #Latvia does not consider the so-called presidential and parliamentary elections in #NagornoKarabakh as legitimate]. Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Latvia. Twitter. 31 March 2020.</ref> [[Turkey]],<ref>[https://www.dailysabah.com/politics/diplomacy/elections-in-upper-karabakh-null-and-void-turkish-foreign-ministry-says Elections in Upper Karabakh null and void, Turkish Foreign Ministry says]. ''[[Daily Sabah]]''. 30 March 2020.</ref> [[Ukraine]],<ref>[http://kyivpost.com/ukraine-politics/ukrinform-ukraine-condemns-elections-in-nagorno-karabakh.html?cn-reloaded=1 UkrInform: Ukraine condemns elections in Nagorno-Karabakh]. ''[[Kyiv Post]]''. 31 March 2020.</ref> and the [[United Kingdom]]<ref>[https://www.news.az/articles/karabakh/147059 UK does not recognize so-called \u201celections\u201d in occupied Azerbaijani territories]. News.az. 1 April 2020.</ref> announced they did not recognise the election and viewed it as counter-productive to the peaceful resolution of the [[Nagorno-Karabakh conflict]].\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Politics}}\n* [[Elections in the Republic of Artsakh]]\n* [[List of political parties in Artsakh]]\n* [[Politics of Artsakh]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Artsakhian presidential elections}}\n{{Artsakhian elections}}\n{{Artsakh topics}}\n[[Category:Elections in the Republic of Artsakh]]\n[[Category:2020 in the Republic of Artsakh]]\n[[Category:2020 elections in Asia|Artsakh]]\n[[Category:2020 elections in Europe|Artsakh]]\n", "text_old": "{{current election}}\n{{Infobox election\n| election_name = 2020 Artsakhian general election\n|